body.text:
Sige, bro. Here’s a **longer casual appreciation message** you can use:

---

Thank you so much, FEU, for being quick to respond and considerate of the situation by moving our face-to-face classes to online synchronous tomorrow, September 17, because of the jeepney transport strike. This really shows how much you value the safety and convenience of us students, as well as the faculty and staff who may also be affected. It’s a huge relief knowing that our learning won’t be disrupted and at the same time, our welfare is prioritized. We truly appreciate how FEU always takes proactive steps to make sure Tamaraws are safe, supported, and able to continue learning despite challenges. 💚💛

---

Gusto mo ba i-tono ko pa ng mas **relatable student vibe** (parang pang-FEU FB group / X post), or keep it **respectful but casual** (pang-comment sa official announcement)?
